          <h3 class="box-title">About online voting</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="box-body" style="font-size: 20px">
          You can vote online provided you have locked your vote for the same through lock vote feature of the website.
          if you have already locked your vote timely, you need to follow the followings
          <ul>
              <li>Login first</li>
              <li>Click online voting</li>
              <li> <strong style="color:red;">Provide voter identification details there</strong>
                   <ul>
                       <li>Voter-Id verification</li>
                       <li>It will check your voter Id for online voting</li>
                       <li>It also check whether you have already casted your vote or not</li>
                       <li>Then it will ask you to supply voting secret given at the time of registration</li>
                       <li>After completing the verification, it will check the voting link validity</li>
                       <li>Lastly, it will check whether there is any election already scheduled in your constituency or not.</li>
                       <li>if each one listed above pass the checks successfully, you will get a ballet paper of your constituency for casting your vote within a specified period of time only.</li>
                       <li> <strong style="color:red;">Vote casting is not allowed once the voting time period is expired even if you are a valid online voter.</strong></li>
                        <li> <strong style="color:red;">If you get your ballet paper after all the verifications, you are able to cast your vote.</strong></li>
                   </ul>
              </li>
              
          </ul>
